parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle when braking can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may suddenly move forward into traffic or crash into obstacles.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly when the brake pedal is applied
the vehicle takes off without warning
the vehicle continues to accelerate despite applying the brake harder
the vehicle crashes into obstacles or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
even when the brake pedal is pressed
and the driver may not be able to slow down or stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system failure can lead to inadequate protection in the event of a crash, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag sensor failure can cause the airbag to malfunction or not deploy in a crash, leading to inadequate protection and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
especially when someone is sitting in the front passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Continental Tire Failure (Tread Separation, Sidewall Bulging, and Cord Separation)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and catastrophic failure of the Continental tires can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden vibration from the tire
tread separation
sidewall bulging
cord separation
and complete tire failure
often resulting in a loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or slip, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a grinding noise
the transmission slips
the vehicle jerks or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to move forward or reverse
the transmission is inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips
the vehicle jerks or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to maintain a consistent speed
the vehicle makes a grinding or whining noise.
